<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 width=80%>
<tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
	<td><font class="pressReleaseBody"><title>Hot New Workstyle Products Help On The Go Executives </title>
<p> January 9, 2000 - The winners of the first official CES Workstyle Awards were announced today at the 2000 International CES. CES showcases the full range of new workstyle products, including digital imaging, wireless devices, Internet access devices, portable peripherals and hand-held navigational equipment.</p>

<p>

Key industry writers were selected to determine this year’s hottest. The three judges for the 2000 CES Workstyle Awards were Ed Baig from USA Today, Bob Parks of Wired, and Linda Lentz with Home. Products were judged on-site at CES, using the following criteria: engineering quality, intended use, unique features, portability, ease of use, design and improvement to the user’s overall workstyle. Products were separated into five categories and one winner was selected from each. 

<p>

The establishment of the workstyle awards comes as a result of the way in which CE products continue to change the way people conduct business. Incorporating technology from the telecom, PC and consumer electronics industries, this new category of products gives workers freedom and flexibility, allowing them to work when and where they want. 

<p>

“These Workstyle award recipients represent the finest aspects of the larger trend in which people are changing the way they do business,” said Robbi Lycett, CES vice president. “They are outstanding examples of the best and most innovative products that keep technologically savvy professionals productive anytime, anywhere.” 

<p>

Digital Imaging The PalmCam from Panasonic (www.panasonic.com) is a new digital still camera that uses both 1.44 MB floppy diskettes and 120MB SuperDisk diskettes capable of storing up to 1500 images. The camera also allows for motion picture recording with audio. 

<p>

Portable Peripherals Think Outside’s (www.thinkoutside.com) Stowaway Portable Keyboard is a full-size keyboard that folds up to about half the size of a Palm or Handspring Visor hand-held computer. The keyboard is specifically designed for use with hand-helds and weighs less than half a pound. 

<p>

Remote Internet Access Devices PCRoomLink (www.pcroomlink.com) is a system of personal computers with high-speed Internet access, installed in hotel rooms across the country, designed to help business travelers be more productive. 

<p>

Wireless The EnGenius SN-900 Ultra is a long range cordless phone and two-way radio. It allows users to roam up to five miles from the base. Each base can support up to nine handsets, allowing an entire work team to stay connected. 

<p>

Hand-Held Navigational Equipment Rand McNally’s (www.randmcnally.com) Street Finder Deluxe 2000 turns Palm IIIs and Palm Vs into Global Positioning Satellite (GPS) units. Users can pinpoint their exact location anywhere in the world and get directions to anywhere they are going. 

<p>

Winners of the 2000 CES Workstyle Awards were announced at a press today, and the winning products will be displayed in a glass kiosk for the remainder of CES in the lobby of the Las Vegas Convention Center. 

<p>

For more news on CES before, during and after the show, return to www.CESweb.org, the interactive source for CES news and information. 

<p>

CEA is a sector of the Electronic Industries Alliance (EIA), the 76-year-old Arlington, Virginia-based trade organization representing all the facets of electronics manufacturing. CEA represent more than 500 U.S. manufacturers of audio, video, accessories, mobile electronics, communication, information technology and multimedia products that are sold through consumer channels. 

<p>

As the sponsor, manager and producer of the International CES – Your Source for Workstyle and Lifestyle TechnologySM, CEA reinvests all profits from CES into industry services, including technical training and education, product promotion, engineering standards development, market research, and governmental and legal affairs support. As the first major technology event of the new millenium, the 2000 International CES is the launch pad for 21st century technology. 




</font></td></tr>



